Rating: 4
I am always trying to find ways to zip up chicken and turkey, since that's all I can eat. I made a huge batch of these -- with two pounds of ground turkey, essentially quintupling all of the ingredients, following the recipe to the letter. The chipotle peppers really made the dish. I mixed it up in the morning so that the seasonings and meat could marinate. Cooked them in the broiler, since it's too cold for grilling, and served them with cheddar cheese, guacamole and a delicious salad. Makes about 12 burgers, so we now have 10 in the freezer for easy dinners in the future.

