Rating: 4
We make these burgers all the time, especially when we have lots of cilantro from the organic farm. They are best with ground turkey thighs (rather than breast meat). My husband doesn't like guacamole, so we usually serve these with roasted red pepper hummus. FYI -- the extra canned chilies keep FOREVER in the fridge, so don't think you have to toss them if you don't you use a whole can.

Rating: 3
These have become a staple in our house all year round. Excellent flavor, and definitely healthier than regular beef burgers. We add sliced avocado and chipotle mayo (mayo, lime juice, cilantro, chipotle peppers and adobo sauce... yum!) and serve on onion rolls. Very easy to make on a busy night when you don't have much time to cook.

